1
00:00:24,156 --> 00:00:28,156
www.titlovi.com

2
00:00:31,156 --> 00:00:35,068
I am Washakie,
of the great Shoshone Nation.

3
00:00:35,120 --> 00:00:39,032
I wish to share with you
the story of Nick Wilson,

4
00:00:39,084 --> 00:00:45,467
or Yagaichi, as he is best
remembered
among the Shoshone people.

5
00:00:45,519 --> 00:00:48,127
The legend
of the white Indian boy

6
00:00:48,179 --> 00:00:51,601
took place within our familiar
valleys and mountains,

7
00:00:51,653 --> 00:00:54,855
known as "Wind River."

8
00:03:21,093 --> 00:03:22,012
Yah!

9
00:03:49,548 --> 00:03:51,009
Damn.

10
00:03:51,061 --> 00:03:52,469
Shoshone.

11
00:03:56,558 --> 00:03:57,601
Aah!

12
00:04:46,834 --> 00:04:49,004
Yagaichi!

13
00:05:15,289 --> 00:05:17,292
He's a comin'.

14
00:05:31,478 --> 00:05:33,596
Take him.

15
00:05:33,648 --> 00:05:36,276
- Pretty good time.
- I’ve e been riding like hell.

16
00:05:38,028 --> 00:05:39,979
What happened to you?

17
00:05:40,031 --> 00:05:42,430
Shoshones.
Pocatello's band again.

18
00:05:42,482 --> 00:05:44,829
- Did you get 'em?
- I didn't have to.

19
00:05:44,881 --> 00:05:46,498
You didn't have to?

20
00:05:46,581 --> 00:05:49,293
Man: Kid, you ain't too smart
taking them Injuns lightly.

21
00:05:49,345 --> 00:05:51,259
Ain't gonna be
safe around here

22
00:05:51,311 --> 00:05:53,121
until they're all
dead and buried.

23
00:05:53,173 --> 00:05:55,760
Yeah, well, as I recall,
they were here first.

24
00:05:57,346 --> 00:06:00,558
Say, that's a nasty one,
we'd better take care of it.

25
00:06:00,610 --> 00:06:02,509
There's a message
from your ma'.

26
00:06:02,561 --> 00:06:04,731
There's some old woman
staying at your house

27
00:06:04,783 --> 00:06:06,733
with a funny name.
Anaba?

28
00:06:06,785 --> 00:06:08,695
Anuba.

29
00:06:09,862 --> 00:06:12,241
- Apparently...
- Don't take that! I got

30
00:06:12,293 --> 00:06:13,200
to go to Grantsville!

31
00:06:16,414 --> 00:06:18,770
Man: Nick. Nick.

32
00:06:18,822 --> 00:06:21,128
N iii-iiick!

33
00:06:21,753 --> 00:06:22,255
Nick! Nick!

34
00:06:28,221 --> 00:06:31,642
- Whoa!
- Hey! It's my turn!

35
00:06:33,937 --> 00:06:35,939
Whoa, aah!

36
00:06:39,903 --> 00:06:41,864
(both laughing)

37
00:06:49,499 --> 00:06:52,920
Nick: Someday I'd like to ride
a real fast horse.

38
00:06:52,972 --> 00:06:55,966
You have trouble
to ride the sheep.

39
00:06:56,018 --> 00:06:58,053
Someday I'll be
a great rider.

40
00:06:58,105 --> 00:06:59,962
(laughing)

41
00:07:00,014 --> 00:07:02,726
Maybe you could learn
on your muuda.

42
00:07:02,778 --> 00:07:04,733
My what?

43
00:07:04,785 --> 00:07:06,689
Muuda.

44
00:07:06,814 --> 00:07:09,558
I taught you.
Donkey.

45
00:07:09,610 --> 00:07:12,217
I'd rather ride
a Bu... bungo,

46
00:07:12,269 --> 00:07:14,825
and be a great
Da... dagwahni.

47
00:07:16,912 --> 00:07:18,914
You learn fast.

48
00:07:18,997 --> 00:07:22,878
But white cannot be great
warriors. Only Indians.

49
00:07:22,930 --> 00:07:25,970
Like my brothers
to the north.

50
00:07:26,022 --> 00:07:29,011
I'll be
a great explorer then,

51
00:07:29,063 --> 00:07:30,889
like Louis and Clark.

52
00:07:31,014 --> 00:07:32,422
Anything
but a sheep-herder.

53
00:07:32,474 --> 00:07:36,939
The great Shoshones
of the Wind River.

54
00:07:36,991 --> 00:07:40,902
My father ride with them.

55
00:07:42,071 --> 00:07:44,929
He tell me
they scalp Crow and Sioux

56
00:07:44,981 --> 00:07:47,787
while they ride
on their horses.

57
00:07:47,839 --> 00:07:49,064
Golly.

58
00:07:49,116 --> 00:07:50,289
Pantsuk,

59
00:07:50,498 --> 00:07:52,501
maybe we could
leave this place.

60
00:07:52,553 --> 00:07:54,410
We could run away.

61
00:07:54,462 --> 00:07:56,465
We could live
with your brothers in the north.

62
00:07:56,517 --> 00:07:58,618
What about our families?

63
00:07:58,670 --> 00:08:00,668
What about the sheep?

64
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:03,432
We can let Sylvester
take care of everything,

65
00:08:03,484 --> 00:08:05,936
since he knows
so much.

66
00:08:08,773 --> 00:08:10,734
Come on,
let's make a pact.

67
00:08:12,528 --> 00:08:16,022
What is pact?

68
00:08:16,074 --> 00:08:19,621
A promise...
or an agreement.

69
00:08:19,673 --> 00:08:21,707
Blood brothers.

70
00:08:22,834 --> 00:08:24,836
Pact.

71
00:08:28,258 --> 00:08:31,804
Lots of hunts,
and fishing.

72
00:08:31,929 --> 00:08:34,641
We'll need horses and packs
for the trip.

73
00:08:35,559 --> 00:08:37,812
And much jerky.

74
00:08:37,864 --> 00:08:40,013
That's for sure.

75
00:08:40,065 --> 00:08:43,695
Pantsuk, you're
my best tsaa hainj.

76
00:08:45,156 --> 00:08:47,867
You are
my best friend, too.

77
00:08:51,539 --> 00:08:53,917
Aah! What'd you
do that for?

78
00:08:54,043 --> 00:08:56,003
I should do worse.
And you...

79
00:08:56,128 --> 00:08:57,901
Why aren't you helping
your father?

80
00:08:57,953 --> 00:08:59,675
- Get goin'.
- Leave him alone.

81
00:08:59,727 --> 00:09:01,218
This is your job...

82
00:09:01,344 --> 00:09:03,587
to make sure the coyotes
don't kill the sheep.

83
00:09:03,639 --> 00:09:06,643
When grown, that lamb
could have kept us for a month.

84
00:09:06,695 --> 00:09:08,468
If I ever catch you
slacking off again,

85
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:11,024
I'll kick your scrawny hide
to Salt Lake and back,

86
00:09:11,076 --> 00:09:12,901
- you hear me?
- I can't do it all by myself.

87
00:09:16,447 --> 00:09:18,742
I hate this place.

88
00:09:49,742 --> 00:09:52,454
(sobbing)

89
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:08,601
Washakie: Before the dreams,

90
00:10:08,726 --> 00:10:10,635
My mother Anuba,

91
00:10:10,687 --> 00:10:13,607
a shaman and healer
among our people,

92
00:10:13,659 --> 00:10:16,528
could not speak
for a very long time.

93
00:10:17,488 --> 00:10:22,286
A mighty avalanche had taken
her two sons, my brothers.

94
00:10:22,338 --> 00:10:25,916
When mother started
having the visions,

95
00:10:25,968 --> 00:10:28,128
the power was understood.

96
00:10:29,379 --> 00:10:31,778
She knew the boy
in her dreams

97
00:10:31,830 --> 00:10:34,178
was good medicine
for our nation.

98
00:10:34,261 --> 00:10:36,723
And we must find him.

99
00:10:36,775 --> 00:10:39,184
I sent my finest warrior,

100
00:10:39,236 --> 00:10:41,478
Morogonai.

101
00:10:50,449 --> 00:10:51,576
(calling)

102
00:11:14,649 --> 00:11:17,569
- What are you looking at?
- Don't do that.

103
00:11:17,621 --> 00:11:20,156
You wanna wake the dead?
Then hush.

104
00:11:24,036 --> 00:11:26,279
- What are you looking at?
- Shh!

105
00:11:26,331 --> 00:11:28,834
It's Louis and Clark
if you must know.

106
00:11:28,886 --> 00:11:30,743
What's it about?

107
00:11:30,795 --> 00:11:33,569
It's about
Louis and Clark.

108
00:11:33,621 --> 00:11:36,344
- Who are they?
- Surveyors.

109
00:11:37,179 --> 00:11:40,048
- What's surveyors?
- Explorers.

110
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:44,146
they mapped out all the western
territory with Sacajawea.

111
00:11:44,198 --> 00:11:46,149
She was a Shoshone.

112
00:11:46,233 --> 00:11:48,590
Shoshones can scalp a person
with one hand

113
00:11:48,642 --> 00:11:50,947
- while riding a horse.
- they ride a horse

114
00:11:51,030 --> 00:11:53,190
- with one hand?
- No,

115
00:11:53,242 --> 00:11:56,308
- they scalp with one hand.
- How do you know?

116
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:59,375
I just do. Listen,
why are you so nosy, anyway?

117
00:11:59,427 --> 00:12:01,378
You writing a book?

118
00:12:01,430 --> 00:12:03,287
Shh, shh.

119
00:12:03,339 --> 00:12:07,010
Why don't you just go to sleep
before you make me catch hell?

120
00:12:07,062 --> 00:12:08,210
Don't cuss, Nick.

121
00:12:08,262 --> 00:12:11,392
Never you mind.
Just go back to sleep.

122
00:12:11,444 --> 00:12:13,503
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight.

123
00:12:13,555 --> 00:12:15,564
- Sleep tight.
- Okay.

124
00:12:15,647 --> 00:12:17,233
Don't let
those bed bugs bite.

125
00:12:17,316 --> 00:12:19,266
I'm gonna bite you.

126
00:12:19,318 --> 00:12:21,488
- Prissy.
- 'Night, Nick.

127
00:12:53,823 --> 00:12:55,826
(signaling)

128
00:13:12,098 --> 00:13:13,433
Nicholas.

129
00:13:16,145 --> 00:13:17,877
(Nick, in haste)
Our Father, bless this food

130
00:13:17,929 --> 00:13:19,556
so it may nourish
and strengthen our bodies

131
00:13:19,608 --> 00:13:21,903
and do us the good we need.
We say these things in the name

132
00:13:21,955 --> 00:13:24,907
- of Jesus Christ, Amen.
- Amen.

133
00:13:24,959 --> 00:13:26,993
I think you s et
a re cord.

134
00:13:28,370 --> 00:13:30,560
Woman: Nicholas.

135
00:13:30,612 --> 00:13:32,751
Criminy, Ma.

136
00:13:36,089 --> 00:13:38,676
I think you boys
are turning into heathens.

137
00:13:40,679 --> 00:13:43,130
It's hotter
than hell out there.

138
00:13:43,182 --> 00:13:46,395
Sylvester, I don't want
any cussing in this house.

139
00:13:46,447 --> 00:13:48,763
If your father were here...

140
00:13:48,815 --> 00:13:50,066
Who do you think
I learned it from?

141
00:13:51,402 --> 00:13:53,644
I never saw ground
so full of rocks.

142
00:13:53,696 --> 00:13:55,907
Yeah, they must be
growing more every y ear.

143
00:13:55,991 --> 00:13:58,703
Ma: Sylvester, your boots
are caked with mud.

144
00:13:58,828 --> 00:14:00,706
Take them outside.

145
00:14:04,544 --> 00:14:06,693
Chicken coop
needs mending.

146
00:14:06,745 --> 00:14:08,790
Chickens got out
last night.

147
00:14:08,842 --> 00:14:11,136
Why you looking at me?
What about Jake?

148
00:14:11,188 --> 00:14:13,457
Just shut up
and mend the fence.

149
00:14:13,509 --> 00:14:15,674
Can't. Got to
watch the sheep.

150
00:14:15,726 --> 00:14:17,478
You'll watch the sheep
after you mend the fence.

151
00:14:17,530 --> 00:14:18,855
Why can't you do it?

152
00:14:18,938 --> 00:14:21,504
- I got to plow.
- Nick: I'll plow.

153
00:14:21,556 --> 00:14:24,018
- You ain't man enough.
- Yes, I am.

154
00:14:24,070 --> 00:14:27,136
You don't even know how,
you dumb jackass.

155
00:14:27,188 --> 00:14:29,801
- That's enough of that.
- Just fix the fence!

156
00:14:29,853 --> 00:14:32,415
If I don't get them crops in,
you don't eat.

157
00:14:32,467 --> 00:14:33,750
Nick: I wouldn't be
missing much.

158
00:14:33,875 --> 00:14:36,170
- You ain't starving, are you?
- I might as well be!

159
00:14:36,222 --> 00:14:38,803
Stop it, you two!
I'll mend the fence.

160
00:14:38,855 --> 00:14:41,333
You got too much work.
Nick'll do it.

161
00:14:41,385 --> 00:14:44,598
He does little else around here.
He'll do it after you eat.

162
00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:46,132
- No!
- I said do it!

163
00:14:46,184 --> 00:14:47,852
You can't tell me what to do,
you're not my father!

164
00:14:47,935 --> 00:14:49,605
I hate it here,
and I hate you!

165
00:14:51,065 --> 00:14:52,108
Eliza Nicholas!

166
00:15:00,995 --> 00:15:03,123
When's father coming home?

167
00:15:03,175 --> 00:15:05,250
Ma: Only
the Good Lord knows.

168
00:15:05,375 --> 00:15:07,754
(chickens clucking)

169
00:15:19,978 --> 00:15:21,648
Nicholas!

170
00:15:22,899 --> 00:15:25,194
Nicholas, no!

171
00:15:25,246 --> 00:15:26,446
Yah!

172
00:15:28,323 --> 00:15:31,693
Nick: Whoa! Ahh!

173
00:15:31,745 --> 00:15:35,834
Benjamin, stop!
Wait, Benjamin!

174
00:15:37,085 --> 00:15:40,215
Nick: Benjamin, stop!
Stop!

175
00:15:42,801 --> 00:15:44,804
Sylvester: Nick, no!

176
00:15:50,019 --> 00:15:54,818
Nick: Help!
Benjamin stop, please stop!

177
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:56,695
Stop!

178
00:16:03,871 --> 00:16:05,123
Nick!

179
00:16:10,046 --> 00:16:11,089
Stop!

180
00:16:27,570 --> 00:16:29,531
(thud)

181
00:16:43,007 --> 00:16:43,842
Man: Our Father
who art in heaven,

182
00:16:45,302 --> 00:16:47,430
hallowed be Thy name.

183
00:16:47,482 --> 00:16:49,558
Thy kingdom come,

184
00:16:49,683 --> 00:16:52,062
Thy will be done,
on earth,

185
00:16:52,114 --> 00:16:54,012
as it is in heaven.

186
00:16:54,064 --> 00:16:56,358
Give us this day
our daily bread,

187
00:16:56,410 --> 00:16:58,601
and forgive us
our trespasses,

188
00:16:58,653 --> 00:17:02,283
as we forgive those
who trespass against us,

189
00:17:02,335 --> 00:17:04,495
and lead us not
into temptation,

190
00:17:04,547 --> 00:17:06,821
but deliver us from evil,

191
00:17:06,873 --> 00:17:09,710
for Thine is the power,
and the kingdom,

192
00:17:09,762 --> 00:17:13,256
and the glory,
forever. Amen.

193
00:17:15,218 --> 00:17:17,846
We dedicate
this final resting place

194
00:17:17,930 --> 00:17:23,302
as a place of peace
and tranquility,

195
00:17:23,354 --> 00:17:25,981
until the morning
of the first resurrection,

196
00:17:27,859 --> 00:17:30,446
in Jesus' holy name,

197
00:17:30,498 --> 00:17:32,449
Amen.

198
00:17:35,161 --> 00:17:38,165
(man singing in
Native American language)

199
00:18:41,375 --> 00:18:44,004
(crying)

200
00:19:14,044 --> 00:19:15,713
Stay back,
I'm warning you!

201
00:19:33,028 --> 00:19:35,198
I'm not a yagaichi!

202
00:19:37,075 --> 00:19:38,484
What you say?

203
00:19:38,536 --> 00:19:41,164
I said I'm not a crier.

204
00:19:44,377 --> 00:19:47,193
You know Shoshone?

205
00:19:47,245 --> 00:19:50,009
No, just some Gosiute.

206
00:19:52,304 --> 00:19:54,494
How you learn?

207
00:19:54,546 --> 00:19:56,685
My friend.

208
00:19:58,980 --> 00:20:00,712
Pantsuk.

209
00:20:00,764 --> 00:20:02,443
Pantsuk.

210
00:20:07,533 --> 00:20:09,274
What are you
gonna do to me?

211
00:20:09,327 --> 00:20:11,975
- Nick: You gonna scalp me?
- Scalp?

212
00:20:12,027 --> 00:20:14,625
Don't you scalp
white people sometimes?

213
00:20:14,677 --> 00:20:17,045
We scalp you?

214
00:20:38,825 --> 00:20:40,775
Aaah! Ahh!

215
00:20:40,828 --> 00:20:43,206
No! No y ell.
No y ell.

216
00:20:43,258 --> 00:20:46,043
I no scalp you.

217
00:20:46,095 --> 00:20:48,630
Be still.

218
00:20:49,798 --> 00:20:52,385
You be still.

219
00:20:59,269 --> 00:21:01,564
Look.

220
00:21:06,988 --> 00:21:10,805
You see him?
He stand tall.

221
00:21:10,857 --> 00:21:14,623
He strong.
You like him?

222
00:21:16,709 --> 00:21:19,421
If you come with us,

223
00:21:19,473 --> 00:21:21,174
you keep him.

224
00:21:23,260 --> 00:21:28,058
- You mean, just leave?
- He is fast.

225
00:21:28,110 --> 00:21:29,936
Fast like the wind.

226
00:21:34,942 --> 00:21:36,893
Are you gonna kidnap me?

227
00:21:36,945 --> 00:21:41,326
- Kidnap?
- Force me to go with you?

228
00:21:41,378 --> 00:21:44,403
Force?
No, no, no.

229
00:21:44,455 --> 00:21:47,459
No, no,
we no force you.

230
00:21:49,253 --> 00:21:52,173
We couldn't just go.
My mother would miss me.

231
00:21:52,225 --> 00:21:53,509
I couldn't hurt her
like that.

232
00:21:59,976 --> 00:22:02,896
We will not take you.

233
00:22:02,948 --> 00:22:05,316
Not take you.

234
00:22:06,234 --> 00:22:09,990
But, maybe...
maybe...

235
00:22:11,366 --> 00:22:14,287
the wind calls you,

236
00:22:15,204 --> 00:22:17,207
and you come.

237
00:22:18,668 --> 00:22:20,753
If you feel

238
00:22:20,805 --> 00:22:22,840
the wind,

239
00:22:24,176 --> 00:22:27,253
you be here

240
00:22:27,305 --> 00:22:29,600
when the sun goes up.

241
00:22:32,227 --> 00:22:33,897
If you no here,

242
00:22:33,980 --> 00:22:36,067
we go.

243
00:22:50,169 --> 00:22:53,089
You are chosen.

244
00:22:54,424 --> 00:22:56,459
Chosen.

245
00:22:56,511 --> 00:22:59,431
You come with us,

246
00:22:59,483 --> 00:23:02,169
you ride this horse.

247
00:23:02,221 --> 00:23:04,855
You learn hunt good.

248
00:23:04,907 --> 00:23:08,010
You live life

249
00:23:08,062 --> 00:23:11,113
like a great man.

250
00:23:14,576 --> 00:23:16,329
Great man.

251
00:23:44,826 --> 00:23:47,955
Morogonai:
The wind calls you.

252
00:23:50,750 --> 00:23:53,045
Pantsuk:
The great Shoshones

253
00:23:53,097 --> 00:23:54,995
of the Wind River.

254
00:23:55,047 --> 00:23:57,759
My father ride with them.

255
00:23:59,512 --> 00:24:01,932
Ma: Nicholas!

256
00:24:04,102 --> 00:24:06,052
Ma: Nicholas!

257
00:24:06,104 --> 00:24:09,108
Morogonai:
The wind calls you.

258
00:25:16,616 --> 00:25:18,994
Female voice:
# close your eyes #

259
00:25:19,046 --> 00:25:22,405
# And see #

260
00:25:22,457 --> 00:25:25,211
# A world awaits you #

261
00:25:25,263 --> 00:25:27,865
# A road sets you free #

262
00:25:27,917 --> 00:25:30,468
# A journey will take you #

263
00:25:30,520 --> 00:25:33,581
# To places unknown #

