654
01:04:47,028 --> 01:04:49,396
Ya ha.

655
01:04:59,200 --> 01:05:01,287
Man: The Mormons
and the Indians

656
01:05:01,339 --> 01:05:02,695
have one spirit Father.

657
01:05:02,747 --> 01:05:05,459
And He is sad
that we fight.

658
01:05:05,542 --> 01:05:07,702
We do not kill
white people.

659
01:05:07,754 --> 01:05:10,758
No, but some
of your brothers do.

660
01:05:13,386 --> 01:05:15,681
Some of yours do also.

661
01:05:15,733 --> 01:05:17,924
Yes.

662
01:05:17,976 --> 01:05:20,354
And our Father in heaven
is full of sorrow.

663
01:05:21,397 --> 01:05:23,849
The white man comes
in peace.

664
01:05:23,901 --> 01:05:27,447
Of course, there are
bad white men,

665
01:05:27,499 --> 01:05:30,159
just as there are
bad Indians.

666
01:05:30,211 --> 01:05:31,984
But for the most part,

667
01:05:32,036 --> 01:05:34,122
these are poor,
honest folk,

668
01:05:34,174 --> 01:05:36,490
searching for a home.

669
01:05:36,542 --> 01:05:38,774
Your friend Brigham
is concerned for you.

670
01:05:38,826 --> 01:05:41,007
He believes
it will not be many snows

671
01:05:41,132 --> 01:05:43,426
before the game
in your country is gone

672
01:05:43,511 --> 01:05:46,640
and there will be no food
for your families.

673
01:05:46,692 --> 01:05:48,465
Would you change
the color of our skin?

674
01:05:48,517 --> 01:05:53,315
Man: No, but we do not desire
for your people to starve.

675
01:05:53,367 --> 01:05:55,402
We will bring
seed and tools,

676
01:05:55,527 --> 01:05:57,018
and teach you
what you must learn.

677
01:05:57,070 --> 01:06:00,930
Send my thanks
to my new friend Big Ham,

678
01:06:00,982 --> 01:06:04,789
and tell him
we will council on his words.

679
01:06:12,299 --> 01:06:14,301
(footsteps)

680
01:06:23,272 --> 01:06:24,816
From brother Brigham.

681
01:06:32,117 --> 01:06:34,537
Brother Brigham wanted
to know your words

682
01:06:34,589 --> 01:06:36,290
about this gift.

683
01:06:37,249 --> 01:06:39,419
This is good.

684
01:06:43,591 --> 01:06:47,763
He wanted to know
how you felt about the gift.

685
01:06:47,815 --> 01:06:50,814
Whites have
words for everything.

686
01:06:50,866 --> 01:06:53,813
But they are just words
from here.

687
01:06:55,482 --> 01:06:57,484
But this...

688
01:06:58,403 --> 01:07:00,197
cannot speak.

689
01:07:17,303 --> 01:07:21,059
Nick: Sir, am I ever going
to find out why I'm here?

690
01:07:21,111 --> 01:07:22,936
Washakie:
Soon, you will know.

691
01:07:23,979 --> 01:07:26,900
But I don't understand.
You don't teach me anything

692
01:07:26,952 --> 01:07:28,985
like medicine,
or war, or the like.

693
01:07:31,906 --> 01:07:33,815
N ever mind.

694
01:07:33,867 --> 01:07:35,870
Soon I will know.

695
01:07:43,463 --> 01:07:45,549
Washakie: For strength.

696
01:07:51,099 --> 01:07:53,268
You should see
my real mother.

697
01:07:53,394 --> 01:07:55,772
She's quite pretty.

698
01:07:56,815 --> 01:07:59,266
Anyway, I think she is.

699
01:07:59,318 --> 01:08:02,968
Nick: She's probably calling
everybody in from the field,

700
01:08:03,020 --> 01:08:06,619
and hollering at Jake,
"Get Blackie outta the house."

701
01:08:06,672 --> 01:08:08,914
Jake has this ugly
old dog and he...

702
01:08:11,209 --> 01:08:13,160
What am I doing?

703
01:08:13,212 --> 01:08:15,172
You don't understand
a word I say.

704
01:08:17,676 --> 01:08:18,636
Yagaichi.

705
01:08:27,690 --> 01:08:30,058
Washakie: When the summer
moved into fall,

706
01:08:30,110 --> 01:08:33,656
we would go to our winter home
to escape the heavy snows.

707
01:08:36,368 --> 01:08:39,706
Yagaichi traveled with us
at a difficult time.

708
01:08:40,749 --> 01:08:43,294
As the snow
came early that y ear,

709
01:08:43,346 --> 01:08:45,839
the hunting grounds
were scarce.

710
01:08:46,799 --> 01:08:49,041
We were forced
even further south,

711
01:08:49,093 --> 01:08:52,640
to find the abundance
needed for our survival.

712
01:09:06,492 --> 01:09:08,109
What is it?

713
01:09:08,161 --> 01:09:11,832
Is what the sky
has told me.

714
01:09:13,585 --> 01:09:15,170
(signaling)

715
01:09:45,294 --> 01:09:46,702
So?

716
01:09:46,754 --> 01:09:48,632
Crows come.
Fight.

717
01:09:48,684 --> 01:09:50,510
Isn't that good?

718
01:09:50,635 --> 01:09:53,587
I do not like fight.

719
01:09:53,639 --> 01:09:56,101
No good comes.
But Crows

720
01:09:56,153 --> 01:09:58,511
will take our horses,

721
01:09:58,563 --> 01:10:03,026
our women. We do not keep
our horses, women,

722
01:10:03,078 --> 01:10:04,644
we will die.

723
01:10:04,696 --> 01:10:07,324
We must go,
make battle.

724
01:11:02,899 --> 01:11:04,902
Nick: Morogonai,

725
01:11:08,031 --> 01:11:09,992
I want you to have this,

726
01:11:11,160 --> 01:11:13,455
for strength.

