Morogonai.

734
01:16:25,333 --> 01:16:27,837
Morogonai?

735
01:16:30,423 --> 01:16:32,509
Morogonai?

736
01:16:33,887 --> 01:16:35,764
Morogonai.

737
01:16:42,231 --> 01:16:44,192
(groaning)

738
01:16:47,237 --> 01:16:49,480
I go now.

739
01:16:49,532 --> 01:16:52,119
- No, I don't want you to go.
- I need go.

740
01:16:56,834 --> 01:16:59,838
I need my father.

741
01:17:01,423 --> 01:17:03,301
Stay here, I'm gonna
go get some help.

742
01:17:03,384 --> 01:17:05,387
No, Yagaichi, no.

743
01:17:07,056 --> 01:17:09,924
Yagaichi,

744
01:17:09,976 --> 01:17:12,980
make a goodbye me now.

745
01:17:16,736 --> 01:17:20,074
I am your friend,

746
01:17:23,620 --> 01:17:25,915
always.

747
01:17:37,514 --> 01:17:39,684
Morogonai.

748
01:18:21,406 --> 01:18:22,992
Identify yourself.

749
01:18:23,075 --> 01:18:26,308
Sylvester Wilson,
from Grantsville,

750
01:18:26,360 --> 01:18:29,490
- Utah territory.
- You wouldn't be kin

751
01:18:29,542 --> 01:18:33,213
- to Elijah Wilson?
- Yes, sir. He's my father.

752
01:18:34,883 --> 01:18:37,386
All I ask is
to share your fire.

753
01:18:40,390 --> 01:18:42,758
please, come.

754
01:18:42,810 --> 01:18:44,896
You're more than welcome.

755
01:18:51,363 --> 01:18:53,908
Man: May we offer you
some fish?

756
01:18:53,960 --> 01:18:56,453
they're small,
but they're tasty.

757
01:18:56,505 --> 01:18:58,456
Thank you, I'm fine.

758
01:18:59,290 --> 01:19:02,577
It'd be a shame
to waste them.

759
01:19:02,629 --> 01:19:05,758
We've already eaten, we'll
leave them for the varmints.

760
01:19:08,470 --> 01:19:10,639
Well, if they'd
just go to waste.

761
01:19:12,517 --> 01:19:16,063
Go ahead, do yourself up.

762
01:19:16,115 --> 01:19:18,306
Thank you.

763
01:19:18,358 --> 01:19:22,447
Thank you. To be honest,
I am still hungry.

764
01:19:25,660 --> 01:19:27,693
So...

765
01:19:27,745 --> 01:19:29,748
tell us, brother Wilson,

766
01:19:29,800 --> 01:19:32,074
you look like...

767
01:19:32,126 --> 01:19:35,172
you've been away from home
for quite a while.

768
01:19:35,224 --> 01:19:36,925
N ear on to 18 months.

769
01:19:38,301 --> 01:19:40,680
I'm searching for my brother.

770
01:19:40,732 --> 01:19:42,213
Your brother?

771
01:19:42,265 --> 01:19:45,185
We think the Indians took him
about two years ago.

772
01:19:45,237 --> 01:19:47,512
Here,

773
01:19:47,564 --> 01:19:49,504
wash it down with this.

774
01:19:49,556 --> 01:19:51,392
Man #2: Which ones?

775
01:19:51,444 --> 01:19:54,574
Don't know.
Can't find a trace of him.

776
01:19:54,626 --> 01:19:56,743
Man #2:
Why would you continue?

777
01:19:58,829 --> 01:20:00,780
Be cause...

778
01:20:00,832 --> 01:20:04,743
I know he's out here.
I can feel it.

779
01:20:04,795 --> 01:20:07,591
So what does this brother
of yours look like?

780
01:20:07,643 --> 01:20:10,808
He'd be about 15 now.

781
01:20:10,860 --> 01:20:13,923
Maybe near my height,

782
01:20:13,975 --> 01:20:15,883
light colored hair,
blue eyes.

783
01:20:15,935 --> 01:20:18,564
Man #2: Last fall we were up
in Wind River country,

784
01:20:18,616 --> 01:20:20,473
up at Washakie's camp.

785
01:20:20,525 --> 01:20:23,862
We saw a young boy
that appeared to be white.

786
01:20:23,914 --> 01:20:27,200
He had light hair.
Didn't get a look at his eyes.

787
01:20:28,786 --> 01:20:31,811
We weren't convinced
he was white.

788
01:20:31,863 --> 01:20:34,784
He was wearing
tribal clothes.

789
01:20:34,836 --> 01:20:37,965
Didn't look like he was
any kind of a prisoner.

790
01:20:38,017 --> 01:20:39,091
Did you find out
his name?

791
01:20:39,300 --> 01:20:41,386
No, didn't have
a chance to ask.

792
01:20:41,511 --> 01:20:42,429
Why didn't you?

793
01:20:44,015 --> 01:20:46,883
I'm sorry.

794
01:20:46,935 --> 01:20:50,690
It's just that l...
It's been so long.

795
01:20:50,742 --> 01:20:53,611
Where is
the Wind River country?

796
01:22:30,408 --> 01:22:31,535
Pocatello!

797
01:23:28,069 --> 01:23:30,437
This was it,
wasn't it?

798
01:23:30,489 --> 01:23:33,702
You have good aim,
my brother.

799
01:23:33,754 --> 01:23:35,788
I was aiming for his head.

800
01:23:41,003 --> 01:23:43,715
Heard it in the wind,
Washakie.

801
01:23:43,767 --> 01:23:46,428
Morogonai could read
